('1', 'Gulf data hub', '', 'Gulf data hub', 'Onfra helps us maintain a secure, trackable, and fully compliant record of every visitor interaction. In our environment, if it\\\\\\\'s not recorded properly, it\\\\\\\'s a risk — Onfra eliminates that risk.', '', '', 'Gulf data hub', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/6887fc6f7b0319913622cfe6_Iterable_lobby_wide.jpg.webp', 'Gulf data hub', '', 'Operated large-scale data centers requiring continuous 24/7 security and operational oversight.\r\n,* Faced difficulty managing high volumes of vendors and maintenance personnel.\r\n,* Manual visitor logs caused inaccurate and delayed data, inefficient access monitoring, and risk of unauthorized entries.\r\n,* No centralized visibility across multiple data center locations.\r\n,* Struggled with compliance and audits due to scattered, manual visitor records.', 'Deployed a centralized, digital visitor management system across all data center facilities. ,*Enabled pre-approved visitor scheduling, self check-in with ID verification, and real-time tracking with alerts. ,*Introduced role-based access permissions to improve control and accountability. ,*Implemented a unified dashboard for complete visibility and faster, informed decisions across all locations.  ,*Automated visitor logs to support compliance, reduce manual effort, and ensure secure and seamless visitor movement.\r\n.', 'Before Onfra, the organization did not have a proper system to manage visitor entries and exits. Each location was maintained individually, and there was no centralized control or validation process in place. They also lacked oversight of the people visiting their premises.,*\r\nAfter implementing Onfra, they gained a complete solution to efficiently manage and monitor visitor entry and exit. The platform provided them with control over visitor scheduling through time slots and enabled centralized management of multiple regional locations from a single dashboard.', 'Ensure seamless digital operations with Gulf Data Hub’s trusted infrastructure. Onfra helps you manage data intelligently so your teams can stay connected, efficient, and scalable across all regions.', 'Gulf Data Hub offers state-of-the-art data center solutions across the Middle East, delivering secure, scalable, and energy-efficient infrastructure for digital growth.', 'Data center', 'UAE ,KSA', '500+', 'Visitor module', '3 years'),
('2', 'Chaitanya', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6840522-2.webp', 'Chaitanya', 'Onfra has transformed how we manage visitor access — everything is now secure, streamlined, and documented. For us, accountability starts at the gate, and Onfra makes it seamless.', '', '', 'Chaitanya', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6840522-2-1.webp', 'Chaitanya', '', 'Operated across multiple locations with no unified visitor management system.,* Relied on manual logbooks for tracking visitor and client entries.,*Faced difficulty maintaining accurate visitor records for audit purposes.,* Lack of centralized control led to inconsistencies in data across sites.,*Struggled to generate timely reports for compliance and internal review.', 'Visitor entry and exit processes were fully digitalized across all sites. ,*Centralized dashboard enabled efficient visitor log management and reporting. ,*Onfra provided audit-ready logs with daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly filters. ,*Enhanced visibility and accountability across multiple client-facing locations. ,*Streamlined compliance process with easily retrievable visitor data.\r\n.', 'Chaitanya was operating a multi-location organization and faced challenges in managing visitor and client visits across different sites, such as FinCrop. They were required to maintain accurate visitor logs for audit purposes.,*\r\nAfter implementing Onfra, their challenges related to visitor entry and exit management were resolved. It became much easier to generate and provide visitor logs for audits, with access to daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly reports at their fingertips.', 'Chainathya relies on Onfra to streamline operations and enhance collaboration across departments. Keep your workflow intuitive and your team focused on delivering impactful results.', 'Discover how Chainathya streamlined internal communication and improved productivity using Onfra’s smart workplace solutions across all departments.', 'Finance', 'Bengaluru', '5000+', 'Visitor module', '3.5 years'),
('3', 'NDPHC', '', 'NDPHC - Niger Delta Power Holding Company', 'With Onfra, our visitor management is no longer manual or prone to gaps. Every visit is logged, compliant, and easy to trace — exactly what our high-security environment demands.', '', '', 'NDPHC', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6852136-1.webp', 'NDPHC', '', 'NDPHC operates multiple high-security power plant sites with large-scale infrastructure. ,*Faced difficulty managing and monitoring visitor entry and exit across all locations. ,*Relied on manual processes, leading to poor visitor tracking and inaccurate logs. ,*Weak access control posed risks in critical infrastructure environments. ,*These issues caused major operational inefficiencies and heightened security threats.', 'Onfra digitalized and centralized the visitor management system across all sites. ,*Enabled self check-in, real-time tracking, automated logs, and strict access controls. ,*Introduced a unified dashboard for full visibility of visitor movement and status. ,*Improved coordination, accountability, and operational efficiency at secure sites. ,*Replaced manual processes with a secure, automated platform ensuring robust security and streamlined operations.', 'NDPHC is a leading power generation company with multiple high-security power plants spread across vast locations. The organization faced considerable challenges in managing visitor flow, relying on manual logbooks that often resulted in inaccurate data, delayed entries, and limited visibility. Given the critical nature of their operations, maintaining strict access control and real-time tracking was essential for ensuring safety and operational efficiency.,*\r\nTo address these issues, Onfra was deployed to modernize the visitor management process. The platform introduced features like self check-in, live tracking, and a centralized dashboard — enabling seamless monitoring of visitor and contractor movement across all sites. With Onfra in place, NDPHC gained a structured and secure system that enhanced coordination, minimized human error, and reinforced safety protocols throughout its facilities.', 'Trusted by NDPHC to maintain critical infrastructure, Onfra ensures every unit of their power ecosystem functions smoothly. It enables smarter coordination, reporting, and performance from anywhere.', 'Learn how NDPHC digitized workflows and improved project oversight with Onfra’s platform, enhancing transparency and collaboration across teams.', 'Energy Generation / Power Plant', 'Nigeria', '500+', 'Visitor module', '1 year'),
('4', 'Grupo Banamiel', '', 'Grupo Banamiel', 'With Onfra, we gained total visibility and control over site access — no more guesswork, no more manual logs. It’s the digital discipline our operations needed.', '', '', 'Grupo Banamiel', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6853073-1.webp', 'Grupo Banamiel', '', 'Operated multiple agricultural sites with high visitor and supplier traffic. ,*Relied on manual logbooks, making it difficult to track and manage visitor data. ,*Missed entries and lack of real-time tracking led to inefficiencies. ,*No centralized system to monitor visitor logs across all farm locations. ,*Faced challenges in maintaining accurate records for compliance and audits.', 'Fully digitalized visitor entry and exit processes across all farm sites. ,*Enabled real-time visitor tracking with accurate and automated data capture. ,*Centralized platform allowed unified monitoring across all locations. ,*Simplified audits and compliance with easily accessible reports (daily, weekly, monthly, yearly). ,*Improved overall operational efficiency and reduced manual workload.', 'Grupo Banamiel is a large-scale farming company operating across multiple agricultural sites. They faced significant challenges in tracking and managing visitor and supplier entries at their various farm locations. With manual processes in place, maintaining accurate visitor records for compliance and audit purposes was both time-consuming and prone to errors.,*\r\nAfter adopting Onfra, Grupo Banamiel streamlined its visitor management system. Entry and exit operations across all farm sites were fully digitalized, allowing real-time tracking and centralized control. The company can now effortlessly generate visitor logs and access detailed reports — daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly — making audits and compliance reporting faster and more reliable.', 'As a global player in agri-export, Grupo Banamiel uses Onfra to simplify operations and ensure team alignment. It keeps logistics, sales, and communication flowing across borders', 'See how Grupo Banamiel modernized operations and boosted cross-location coordination by adopting Onfra\\\'s secure cloud workspace tools..', 'Farming Industry', 'Dominican Republic', '1000+', 'Visitor module', '5 years'),
('5', 'Vidya Herbs', '', 'Vidya Herbs - Committed to Nature', 'Onfra helped us create a secure and compliant visitor experience, from check-in to exit. The simplicity and traceability it offers make all the difference.', '', '', 'Vidya Herbs', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6853194-1.webp', 'Vidya Herbs', '', 'Visitor and vendor movements were tracked using manual logbooks, leading to inefficiencies. ,*Missed entries and delays were common due to the lack of a systematic process. ,*No real-time visibility into who was entering or exiting the premises. ,*Managing data across multiple production and research facilities was time-consuming and error-prone. ,*Difficulty in generating daily or location-wise visitor reports.', 'Visitor entry and exit processes were fully digitalized across all locations. ,*Real-time tracking enabled better control and oversight of site movements. ,*A centralized platform was introduced to manage all locations from one place. ,*Daily visitor reports and analytics became easily accessible through the dashboard. ,*Operational efficiency improved with streamlined visitor flow and enhanced visibility.', 'Vidya Herbs is a herbal manufacturing company operating across multiple production and research facilities. The team faced challenges in managing and tracking visitor and vendor movements at various locations. Manual logbooks often led to missed entries, delays, and a lack of real-time visibility.,*\r\nAfter implementing Onfra, the company streamlined its visitor management process. Entry and exit operations across all sites were digitalized, enabling real-time tracking and centralized control. Onfra now allows the team to efficiently manage visitor flows and access detailed reports — daily from a single platform, improving operational efficiency and oversight.', 'At Vidya Herbs, natural wellness meets modern efficiency with Onfra. Collaborate seamlessly across research, production, and sales for optimized herbal product delivery.', 'Discover Vidya Herbs, a global leader in herbal extracts and natural solutions. With a commitment to sustainability and innovation, Vidya Herbs provides high-quality plant-based ingredients for food, cosmetics, nutraceuticals, and pharmaceuticals.', 'Herbal Manufacturing Company', 'Multi-location', '200-500', 'Visitor module', '6+ years'),
('6', 'Maithan Ceramic Limited', '', 'Maithan Ceramic Limited', 'For a high-security, high-volume facility like ours, Onfra ensures every visitor is accounted for, verified, and tracked — without slowing down operations.', '', '', 'Maithan Ceramic Limited', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6854187-2.webp', 'Maithan Ceramic Limited', '', 'Multiple manual logbooks were used for visitors, goods vehicle movements, and departmental logs, making operations error-prone. ,*Lack of a centralized system led to poor tracking and inefficient coordination across locations. ,*Difficulty in monitoring offloading times for goods vehicles. ,*No separate or streamlined process for managing third-party labor or vendors. ,*Inability to accurately track contractor labor entries/exits based on shift timings.', 'Visitor, goods vehicle, and departmental entry/exit logs were fully digitized and centralized. ,*Real-time tracking improved coordination and eliminated manual tracking errors. ,*Onfra’s Visitor Module enabled smooth management and monitoring of goods vehicle movements. ,*Flexi Pass module allowed accurate tracking of third-party labor and vendors. ,*Labor entries/exits are now monitored effectively based on shift timings, improving control and visibility.', 'The client is a ceramic manufacturing company with multiple facilities operating across pan-India. They were facing significant challenges in their front-office operations — particularly in managing the entry and exit of visitors, third-party labor, and goods vehicles. Relying on manual processes led to inefficiencies, missed records, and a lack of real-time visibility across locations.,*\r\nAfter implementing Onfra, the organization streamlined and systemized its entry and exit operations. Visitor, contractor, and goods vehicle movements are now digitally managed, with real-time tracking and centralized control. Onfra has brought structure and efficiency to the client’s operations, enabling smoother coordination across all their manufacturing sites.', 'Maithan, a leader in ceramic manufacturing, uses Onfra to manage complex processes with ease. Empower your workforce to stay in sync across locations, timelines, and tasks.', 'Maithan streamlined facility management and enhanced employee safety by adopting Onfra’s smart workplace automation.', 'Ceramic Manufacturing Industry', 'West Bengal', '200-500', 'Visitor and Flexi Pass module', '1 year'),
('7', 'Decibels and Pixels Solutions Private Limited', '', 'Decibels and Pixels Solutions Private Limited', 'Onfra streamlined our entry and exit workflows with precision. Now, every visit is verified, logged, and secure — without disrupting our pace of work.', '', '', 'Decibels & Pixels Solutions Private Limited', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6855179-1.webp', 'Decibels & Pixels Solutions Private Limited', '', 'Difficulty in tracking technician attendance during fieldwork. ,*No real-time visibility into technician movements or job site presence. ,*Inability to monitor work hours and task completion accurately. ,*Lack of accountability for on-site technician activities. ,*Inefficiencies in managing and coordinating field operations.', 'Introduced a real-time attendance tracking module. ,*Enabled geo-tagging to monitor technician locations accurately. ,*Implemented geo-fencing to verify presence at job sites. ,*Improved visibility into technician movements and task progress. ,*Enhanced overall coordination, accountability, and performance tracking.', 'The client is a company operating in the AV & IT solutions industry, with a large team of technicians deployed for on-site fieldwork. One of their key challenges was efficiently managing technician attendance and monitoring their real-time location during field assignments. Without a proper system in place, it was difficult to track technician presence, task progress, and site-level accountability.,*\r\nAfter implementing Onfra, the client gained a powerful real-time tracking solution integrated with geo-tagging and geo-fencing functionalities. This allowed them to accurately monitor technician movements, record attendance based on actual location, and ensure improved visibility and control over their field operations. As a result, overall coordination, accountability, and technician performance tracking became more streamlined and reliable.', 'Decibels & Pixels Solutions Private Limited enhances its creative and operational excellence through Onfra. Whether it\\\'s design, strategy, or execution, everything stays connected under one powerful platform.', 'Decibels & Pixels Solutions Private Limited transformed their workspace efficiency by implementing Onfra’s digital solutions for seamless access control, asset tracking, and employee collaboration.', 'A/V and IT Solution Providers', 'Chennai', '20+', 'Employee Attendance', '1 year'),
('8', 'IT Park', '', 'IT Park', 'Managing a high-footfall tech campus requires agility and control. Onfra gave us both, with a seamless visitor experience and centralized oversight.', '', '', 'IT Park', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ChatGPT-Image-Aug-26-2025-03_04_07-PM-1.webp', 'IT park', '', 'A serious security incident occurred involving the misuse of a female visitor’s contact information. ,*Visitor data was being recorded manually in unsecured logbooks. ,*The breach led to a police investigation, highlighting severe privacy risks. ,*Lack of access control made sensitive visitor data vulnerable to misuse. ,*Overall trust and safety standards at the IT Park were compromised.', 'Digitized the entire visitor management system to eliminate manual data handling. ,*Implemented access-controlled and encrypted storage for visitor information. ,*Restricted data access through defined user roles to ensure privacy compliance. ,*Protected sensitive contact details from unauthorized exposure. ,*Helped restore trust and significantly strengthened data security and visitor safety.', 'The client is an IT Park housing multiple organizations and receiving a high volume of daily visitors. They faced a serious security incident involving the mishandling of a female visitor’s personal details, which were recorded in a manual logbook. This breach led to a police investigation and raised urgent concerns about data privacy and the safety of visitors on the premises.,*\r\nFollowing this incident, Onfra was brought in to digitize and secure the entire visitor management process. With features like access-controlled data storage, encrypted visitor information, and restricted user roles, Onfra enabled the IT Park to ensure that sensitive visitor data — especially contact details — remained protected. The implementation of Onfra not only helped prevent future breaches but also restored trust in the organization’s commitment to security and privacy.', 'Onfra brings clarity and control to fast-paced IT Parks by helping teams collaborate, share updates, and operate securely from a centralized workspace.', 'Onfra helped the IT Park centralize operations across multiple buildings with intelligent infrastructure and real-time occupancy monitoring tools.', 'IT Park', 'Chennai', '10,000+', 'Visitor module', '3 years'),
('9', 'Co working Space', '', 'Co working Space', 'Onfra helps us maintain a seamless flow of guests and professionals with real-time tracking and contactless check-ins — perfect for a dynamic workspace.', '', '', 'Co-working Space', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/1000028042-1.webp', 'Co-working Space', '', 'The client faced an unannounced police inspection requesting visitor and ID details. ,*Due to a manual log system, the organization could not provide accurate visitor information. ,*There was no verification method for confirming visitor identities. ,*The absence of ID proof records raised compliance and security concerns. ,*The police advised implementation of a secure and verifiable visitor management system.', 'Deployed a centralized, secure visitor management system across all locations. ,*Enabled OTP-based visitor identity verification for real-time authentication. ,*Integrated government-issued ID card scanning to capture verified details. ,*Ensured accurate, traceable, and compliant visitor records at all times. ,*Strengthened organizational accountability and met police-recommended security standards.', 'The client is a co-working space provider operating across multiple locations, catering to a large number of daily visitors and clients booking workspaces. As traffic increased, managing visitor details manually became a challenge. The issue escalated when the local police department made an unannounced visit to request information about a suspected individual. Due to the limitations of their manual log system, the client was unable to provide accurate or verified visitor records, which raised serious compliance and security concerns.,*\r\nFollowing this incident, the police department strictly advised the organization to implement a system capable of verifying visitor identities through OTP validation and capturing government-issued ID cards. To address this, the client adopted Onfra, a secure and centralized visitor management system. With features like real-time data capture, OTP-based verification, and ID scanning, Onfra enabled the organization to maintain accurate, verified records across all locations — ensuring compliance, safety, and peace of mind.', 'Stay organized, connected, and productive in your co-working ecosystem with Onfra. Help tenants and managers sync effortlessly — so every desk and meeting room runs at full potential.', 'This Co-working Space elevated the member experience and space utilization by integrating Onfra’s customizable workplace and visitor management platform.', 'Real Estate', 'Bengaluru', '50+', 'Visitor module', '1 year'),
('10', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt Ltd', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6877705-1.webp', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd.', 'With Onfra, we’ve gained better control over who enters our premises — every interaction is logged, secure, and streamlined for daily operations.', '', '', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd.', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6915306-1.webp', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd.', '', 'No centralized system to manage visitor data across multiple client locations. ,*Continued use of manual logbooks led to inconsistent visitor records, delayed reporting, and limited real-time visibility into visitor movement. ,*Overall lack of transparency, control, and efficiency in visitor management operations. ,*Difficulty in accurately recording and consolidating visitor entry and exit data. ,*Manual logbooks caused accountability issues and reduced operational efficiency.', 'Implemented a smart visitor management platform to replace manual logbooks. ,*Enabled real-time tracking of visitors across all client locations. ,*Digital data capture ensured accuracy and consistency of visitor records. ,*Centralized monitoring provided complete visibility and control across sites. ,*Improved transparency, responsiveness, and accountability in visitor management. ,*Streamlined operations and enhanced service delivery across the client network.', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd. is a service provider managing front-office and security operations across multiple client locations. One of their key challenges was accurately recording and consolidating visitor entry and exit data. Manual logbooks led to inconsistent records, delayed reporting, and a lack of centralized visibility — impacting both operational efficiency and accountability.,*\r\nTo overcome these challenges, Lumiere Security implemented Onfra, a smart visitor management platform that enabled real-time tracking, digital data capture, and centralized monitoring across all sites. With Onfra in place, Lumiere Security enhanced the accuracy, transparency, and responsiveness of their operations — ensuring streamlined visitor management and improved service delivery across their client network.', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd. blends creativity and management on Onfra’s workspace. Streamline your production timelines, team reviews, and communications under one intuitive dashboard.', 'Lumiere Security Services Pvt. Ltd. optimized its office operations and improved visitor experience using Onfra’s smart workplace management solutions.', 'Security Management', 'Chennai', '500+', 'Visitor module', '1 year'),
('11', 'Precision Equipments', '', 'Precision Equipments', 'Managing vendor and visitor access at our equipment facility is now smarter and more secure thanks to Onfra’s tailored and robust solution.', '', '', 'Precision Equipments', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6879379-1.webp', 'Precision Equipments', '', 'Relied on manual, paper-based processes for visitor passes and appointment confirmations. ,*Used physical pagers and handwritten logs, causing delays and inefficiencies. ,*Lacked visibility across multiple manufacturing locations. ,*Outdated front-office processes reduced coordination and overall efficiency.', 'Implemented a digital, paperless, centralized front-office platform. ,*Enabled quick appointment verification and seamless visitor check-ins. ,*Provided real-time coordination across all manufacturing units. ,*Improved efficiency, data accuracy, visibility, and reliability of front-office operations.', 'Precision Equipments is a multi-location manufacturing company that relied on manual, paper-based processes to manage visitor passes and appointment confirmations. The system involved using physical pagers and handwritten logs, resulting in delays, inefficiencies, and a lack of visibility across their front-office operations.,*\r\nTo modernize this process, the company implemented Onfra across all its manufacturing units. The platform replaced manual visitor handling with a digital, centralized system — enabling quick appointment verification, seamless visitor check-ins, and improved coordination across locations. With Onfra, Precision Equipments significantly enhanced the speed, accuracy, and efficiency of its front-office operations.', 'Precision Equipments relies on Onfra to maintain high standards across equipment manufacturing, support, and logistics. Achieve accuracy in every task with unified work tracking.', 'Precision Equipments enhanced asset visibility and streamlined facility workflows by deploying Onfra’s real-time monitoring tools.', 'Manufacturing Company', 'Chennai', '500+', 'Visitor module', '2+ years'),
('12', 'Ascend International School', '', 'Ascend International School', 'Onfra gives us peace of mind by ensuring only verified visitors can access school grounds—safeguarding our students while simplifying admin tasks.', '', '', 'Ascend International School', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6901109-1.webp', 'ASCEND International School', '', 'Relied on multiple manual logbooks to track visitors other than students and staff. ,*Records were disorganized, inconsistent, and difficult to retrieve accurately. ,*No centralized system for real-time monitoring or access control. ,*Limited ability to manage and secure non-student/staff visitors effectively.', 'Deployed a centralized, digital visitor management system. ,*Introduced secure check-in with ID validation for all non-student/staff visitors. ,*Enabled real-time visitor tracking and centralized monitoring. ,*Improved security, visibility, and administrative control at the entry point.', 'Ascend International School, a reputed educational institution, was managing visitor entries using multiple manual logbooks at a single entry point. This made it difficult to track and manage visitors other than students and staff—such as parents, vendors, and guests—leading to disorganized records and limited visibility.,*\r\nTo overcome this, the school implemented Onfra, a digital visitor management platform. Onfra replaced manual processes with a centralized system, enabling secure check-ins, ID validation, and real-time visitor tracking. This transformation brought structure, improved security, and allowed the administration to efficiently manage and monitor all external visitors from a single point of control.', 'Ascend International School uses Onfra to manage academics, administration, and parent communication. Foster an organized and high-performing learning environment.', 'Ascend International School upgraded campus security and visitor tracking with Onfra’s centralized digital access and ID management system.', 'Educational Institution', 'Mumbai', '100+', 'Visitor module', '1.5+ years'),
('13', 'GVK Industries Limited', '', 'GVK Industries Limited', 'Onfra transformed our multi-site visitor coordination with real-time validation, purpose-based access, and shift-specific controls—boosting security and clarity.', '', '', 'GVK', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ChatGPT-Image-Aug-27-2025-04_35_46-PM-1.webp', 'GVK', '', 'Faced communication gaps and operational delays at the front office of their petrochemical manufacturing unit. ,*Lacked real-time visibility into visitor data across multiple locations. ,*Struggled to manage restricted area access and issue timely, purpose-based visitor passes. ,*Traditional processes caused coordination issues and security concerns, especially around shift-based access.', 'Deployed a centralized digital visitor management system across all locations. ,*Enabled real-time tracking of visitor movement, purpose-based digital badges, and access controls for restricted zones. ,*Introduced shift-specific pass issuance, aligning with day/time schedules for better control. ,*Improved operational efficiency, security, and administrative clarity across all facilities.', 'GVK, a prominent petrochemical manufacturing company, was struggling with fragmented visitor management systems across its multiple locations. The front office operations lacked real-time visibility and control over visitor movement, leading to communication gaps and security concerns—especially when managing restricted areas. Traditional processes made it difficult to issue timely passes or identify visitors based on the purpose and shift timings.\r\nTo address these challenges, GVK partnered with Onfra, which provided a centralized, digital solution. Onfra enabled real-time tracking of visitor entries and exits, issued purpose-based digital badges, and introduced shift-specific passes to streamline access management. This transformation not only enhanced operational efficiency but also strengthened GVK’s security protocol across all its manufacturing units.', 'From infrastructure to energy, GVK drives large-scale coordination with Onfra. Ensure smooth execution across departments with secure, real-time collaboration.', 'GVK implemented Onfra’s smart infrastructure tools to modernize facility access, improve compliance, and manage workforce operations efficiently.', 'Petrochemical Manufacturing Company', 'Uttarakhand', '100+', 'Visitor module and Flexi Pass module', '1 + years'),
('14', 'Khosla Profil Pvt Ltd', '', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd.', 'Onfra digitized our entry process with zero hardware dependency. It’s now easier to verify, track, and manage visitors across our industrial units.', '', '', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd.', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-69061801-1.webp', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd.', '', 'No centralized system to manage visitor data across multiple manufacturing units.\r\n,*Manual logbooks created inefficiencies in managing visitor data, often resulting in incomplete records and the lack of real-time visibility.\r\n,*Managing visitor information across multiple sites was fragmented and time-consuming due to the absence of a unified system.\r\n,*The process made it difficult to maintain compliance records and meet audit requirements efficiently.\r\n,*Security teams lacked quick access to visitor information, which limited their ability to respond to queries or incidents.\r\n,*The use of paper-based methods led to delays in reporting and an increased risk of data loss or errors.', 'Implemented a smart visitor management platform to replace manual logbooks.\r\n,*Visitor entry and exit operations were fully digitalized, enabling accurate data capture and real-time tracking, improving both security and efficiency.\r\n,*A centralized platform was introduced, allowing seamless monitoring and management of visitor logs across all locations from a single dashboard, greatly simplifying audits and reporting.\r\n,*Automated workflows enabled real-time approvals and digital visitor passes, ensuring faster and more secure access control.\r\n,*Security and admin staff could now view live visitor movements and activity logs, enabling better situational awareness and response.\r\n,*Emergency roll-call reports were made available at a click, helping identify every visitor inside the premises in real time.\r\n,*The digital system ensured better compliance with audit protocols, making Khosla Profil audit-ready and aligned with global standards.', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd., operating multiple manufacturing units across India, faced challenges in centralizing their front-office operations. Managing visitors and non-employees through manual registers and physical visitor passes led to delays, confusion, and inconsistencies — especially when confirming meetings with the concerned personnel across various locations.,*\r\nTo overcome this, Khosla Profil adopted Onfra’s digital visitor management solution. The system enabled them to generate visitor badges digitally, confirm appointments in real time, and assign access based on the visitor’s purpose — eliminating manual signatures and paperwork. This streamlined their operations, improved coordination across units, and enhanced security and accountability at all entry points.', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd. ensures precise industrial processes and collaboration using Onfra. Keep manufacturing, planning, and communications running like clockwork.', 'Khosla Profil Pvt. Ltd. streamlined its factory access and workforce tracking using Onfra’s digital facility management system.', 'Fabric Manufacturing Company', 'Mumbai', '500+', 'Visitor module', '2 years'),
('15', 'Hasbro Clothing Pvt Ltd', NULL, 'Hasbro Clothing Pvt. Ltd.', 'Onfra delivered a QR-based visitor system that works on our existing infrastructure — efficient, contactless, and ideal for our minimalist front desk.', '', '', 'Hasbro Clothing Pvt. Ltd.', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6906288-1.webp', 'Hasbro Clothing Pvt. Ltd.', '', 'Limited front desk space for extra devices.\n,*Device maintenance issues causing operational delays.\n,*High dependency on physical tools for visitor management.\n,*Logistical and maintenance challenges with kiosks, biometrics, or RFID systems.\n,*Need for a seamless solution using existing desktops and browsers.\n,*Desire to preserve minimalistic front desk setup without infrastructure changes.', 'Implemented a contactless, QR-based visitor management system.\n,*Works on existing desktop setups and web browsers.\n,*No dependency on external hardware or physical devices.\n,*Real-time visitor tracking and automatic logs.\n,*Purpose-based visitor tracking for better control.\n,*Improved operational efficiency with minimal manual intervention.\n,*Aligned with Hasbro’s infrastructure and design preferences.', 'Hasbro, a growing clothing brand, was looking to streamline its front-office operations without relying on additional hardware or physical devices. The traditional approach of installing check-in kiosks, biometric systems, or RFID scanners posed logistical and maintenance challenges. Hasbro needed a lightweight, cost-effective, and efficient solution that could manage visitor flow while preserving their minimalistic front desk setup.,*\nTo address this, Onfra deployed a fully contactless, QR-based visitor management system that worked effortlessly using existing devices like computers and smartphones. The system enabled real-time check-in and check-out, automatic visitor logs, and purpose-based tracking — all without the need for extra hardware. This approach improved operational efficiency, ensured better visitor control, and aligned perfectly with Hasbro’s infrastructure and design preferences.', 'Join leading lifestyle brands like Hasbro Clothing in empowering teams with seamless collaboration through Onfra — where creativity meets productivity.', 'Hasbro Clothing Pvt. Ltd. improved warehouse efficiency and staff movement control with Onfra’s smart access and operations platform.', 'Clothing Manufacturing Company', 'Chennai', '500+', 'Visitor module', '1+ years'),
('16', 'IT Radiant', '', 'IT Radiant — Enabling the Enterprise of the Future', 'Onfra helped us replace manual registers with a secure, digital check-in system that validates visitors through OTP, keeping our entry points efficient, secure, and compliant.', '', '', 'IT Radiant', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6906358-1.webp', 'IT Radiant', '', 'Reliance on manual registers for entry and exit processes.\r\n,*Lack of real-time tracking and accurate visitor records.\r\n,*No seamless visitor experience, leading to delays and inefficiency.\r\n,*Security concerns due to absence of OTP-based identity verification.\r\n,*Risk of unauthorized access without proper visitor validation.\r\n,*Urgent need for a reliable and secure digital check-in system.', 'Implemented a secure, digital visitor management system with OTP-based authentication.\r\n,*Enabled digital recording of all visitor details to maintain accurate logs.\r\n,*Validated each visitor’s identity to ensure authenticity and prevent unauthorized access.\r\n,*Enhanced traceability and access control without requiring additional hardware.\r\n,*Streamlined visitor flow and front desk operations for greater efficiency.\r\n,*Delivered a professional and secure workplace entry experience.', 'IT Radiant wanted to modernize its entry and exit process by eliminating manual logbooks and introducing a secure, digital system. Their key requirement was to validate each visitor through OTP verification to ensure authenticity and prevent unauthorized access. The existing system lacked real-time tracking, accurate records, and a seamless visitor experience — making the need for a reliable solution urgent.,*\r\nOnfra provided a simple yet robust visitor management system that records all visitor details digitally and verifies identities through OTP-based validation. The solution not only improved security and traceability but also streamlined front desk operations without the need for extra hardware. This upgrade aligned perfectly with IT Radiant’s vision for a professional, efficient, and future-ready workplace environment.', 'Boosted enterprise agility with Onfra’s unified workspace — streamlining operations, reducing silos, and powering next-gen IT services.', 'IT Radiant leveraged Onfra’s enterprise solutions to digitize access control, visitor management, and compliance monitoring across its facilities.', 'Outsourcing Company', 'Bengaluru', '500+', 'Visitor module', '2 years'),
('17', 'HAWORTH', '', 'HAWORTH', 'Onfra bridged our visitor–host communication gap with instant notifications, improving coordination and enhancing visitor management across our manufacturing facilities.', '', '', 'HAWORTH', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6907157-1.webp', 'HAWORTH', '', 'Communication gaps during visitor interactions at manufacturing units.\r\n,*Visitors often arrived without hosts being notified in time.\r\n,*Resulting delays and confusion in coordinating meetings.\r\n,*No streamlined process for prior visitor notifications.\r\n,*Lack of real-time communication between visitors and concerned staff.\r\n,*Need for improved workplace security and coordination.', 'Implemented a comprehensive digital visitor management system.\r\n,*Automated the entire visitor check-in process.\r\n,*Sent instant notifications to both hosts and visitors for better coordination.\r\n,*Eliminated manual delays and improved real-time communication.\r\n,*Enhanced visitor experience, workplace security, and operational efficiency.\r\n,*Increased staff accountability across manufacturing units.', 'Haworth, a global manufacturing company, was facing significant communication gaps during visitor interactions at their production facilities. Visitors often arrived without the host being notified in time, causing delays and confusion. The company needed a streamlined system to ensure prior notifications and smooth coordination between visitors and staff.,*\r\nOnfra implemented a digital visitor management system that automated the entire check-in process. With instant notifications to both hosts and visitors, the solution eliminated manual delays and enabled real-time communication. This not only enhanced the visitor experience but also boosted security, operational efficiency, and staff accountability across Haworth’s wide-ranging manufacturing units.', 'Elevated workplace innovation with secure document access, real-time updates, and frictionless internal communication.', 'HAWORTH transformed its office space efficiency and visitor experience by integrating Onfra’s smart workplace solutions.', 'Furniture Manufacturing Company', 'Chennai', '200+', 'Visitor module', '2 years'),
('18', 'KKCL', '', 'KKCL — Kewal Kiran Clothing Limited', 'With Onfra’s pre-invite and appointment modules, our visitor flow is now streamlined, structured, and smarter across all touchpoints.', '', '', 'Kewal Kiran Clothing Limited (KKCL)', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/home-store-1.webp', 'Kewal Kiran Clothing Limited (KKCL)', '', 'Manual coordination for visitor management causing inefficiencies.\r\n,*Lack of a structured system leading to unplanned visits.\r\n,*Delayed host notifications affecting meeting readiness.\r\n,*Inefficient front-desk operations and longer wait times.\r\n,*Need to improve security and coordination between visitors and hosts.', 'Onfra implemented a smart visitor management system with pre-invite functionality and appointment scheduling modules.\r\n,*Streamlined entry procedures for a more organized and efficient visitor experience.\r\n,*Enabled real-time host notifications to ensure timely coordination.\r\n,*Improved planning for both visitors and the organization.\r\n,*Reduced wait times, enhanced security, and boosted overall efficiency across locations.', 'KKCL wanted to streamline and digitize their visitor management process by introducing pre-invite and appointment scheduling features. Their goal was to reduce wait times, improve security, and ensure smoother coordination between visitors and hosts.,*\r\nOnfra addressed this need by providing a smart visitor management system with pre-invite functionalities and appointment modules, enabling hassle-free entry, real-time host notifications, and better planning for both visitors and the organization.', 'From shop floor to boardroom, Onfra helped unify KKCL’s teams for faster decision-making and streamlined manufacturing processes.', 'KKCL enhanced access security and digitized employee movement across its manufacturing units using Onfra’s centralized platform.', 'Clothing Manufacturing Company', 'Mumbai', '1000+', 'Visitor module', '1 year'),
('19', 'Dynamic Logistics', '', 'Dynamic Logistics — Innovating Inventories', 'Onfra helped us digitize and streamline warehouse and office reception operations — enhancing visibility, control, and communication in real time.', '', '', 'Dynamic Logistics', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6914930-1.webp', 'Dynamic Logistics', '', 'Lack of a centralized system for managing goods, vehicles, and visitors across warehouses.\r\n,*Operational inefficiencies and delayed communication between teams.\r\n,*Difficulty in tracking real-time activities at multiple locations.\r\n,*Security and accountability challenges due to manual entry systems.\r\n,*Inaccurate records impacting productivity and coordination.', 'Onfra implemented a comprehensive digital visitor, vehicle, and goods management system.\r\n,*Digitized entry and exit procedures for staff, visitors, and vehicles.\r\n,*Enabled real-time tracking and automated approvals for smooth operations.\r\n,*Centralized data management for better visibility and decision-making.\r\n,*Improved security, transparency, and coordination across all logistics touchpoints.', 'Dynamic Logistics operates a wide network of warehouses where managing the movement of goods, vehicles, and visitors is crucial to daily operations. Previously, the company faced challenges with manual entry systems, which led to inefficiencies, delays, and difficulties in maintaining accurate records. The lack of a centralized process made it hard to track logistics in real time, directly affecting both productivity and security.,*\r\nTo address this, Onfra implemented a comprehensive digital visitor and logistics management solution. The system streamlined front office operations by digitizing entry and exit procedures for staff, visitors, and vehicles. With features such as real-time tracking, automated approvals, and centralized data management, Dynamic Logistics significantly improved its operational efficiency, reduced bottlenecks, and enhanced overall warehouse coordination.', 'Enabled end-to-end logistics visibility and coordination — reducing delays, miscommunication, and operational overhead.', 'Dynamic Logistics adopted Onfra’s solutions to streamline vehicle entry, driver check-ins, and dock-level operations for faster turnaround.', 'Logistics Company', 'Pune', '200–500', 'Visitor module', '1 year'),
('20', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6915306-1.webp', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics', 'Onfra made our shift from manual logbooks to a digital visitor platform effortless — giving us accuracy, accountability, and control at every entry point.', '', '', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics', 'https://onfra.io/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ai-render-6915306-1.webp', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics', '', 'Reliance on manual logbooks for tracking visitors, vehicles, and goods.\r\n,*Delayed entries and data inconsistencies affecting operations.\r\n,*Limited visibility into real-time activities across locations.\r\n,*Inefficiencies impacting operational speed, security, and decision-making as the company scaled.\r\n,*Manual processes becoming inefficient and error-prone with expansion.', 'OnFRA implemented a fully digitized visitor and logistics management system,*IEnabled real-time tracking of goods, vehicles, and visitors across all facilities,*ICentralized operations for improved visibility and coordination,*IStreamlined check-ins to enhance efficiency and reduce delays,*Improved data accuracy, security, and scalability for future growth.', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics, a growing logistics provider, faced delays, data inaccuracies, and limited visibility due to its reliance on manual logbooks for tracking visitors, vehicles, and goods across multiple locations. As the company expanded, managing these operations manually became increasingly inefficient and error-prone.,*\r\nTo resolve this, Caravan Cargo partnered with Onfra to digitize its front office and warehouse processes. Onfra’s centralized system enabled real-time tracking, streamlined check-ins, and improved data accuracy — enhancing efficiency, security, and scalability across all facilities.', 'Trusted by Caravan Cargo Logistics to simplify communication and document sharing across logistics hubs — so their teams can deliver faster, collaborate better, and keep freight moving without delays.', 'Caravan Cargo Logistics improved real-time cargo monitoring and facility control with Onfra’s logistics-friendly digital management system.', 'Logistics Company', 'Mumbai', '50+', 'Visitor module', '1 year');
